CONTEXT: T026 — WhatsApp webhook receiver. Entry point for all resident WhatsApp messages. Must handle Meta's webhook verification handshake (GET) and inbound message processing (POST) with HMAC-SHA256 signature validation.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Supabase Edge Function (would require separate deployment, different auth pattern)
  2. Next.js API route at /api/webhooks/whatsapp (selected) — consistent with existing API pattern, same deployment pipeline, access to supabaseAdmin and Redis
  3. Vercel Edge Function (faster cold start but limited Node.js APIs for crypto)
DECISION: Four new files created. lib/whatsapp/types.ts — full Meta Cloud API webhook payload types + normalized InboundWhatsAppMessage interface. lib/whatsapp/verify.ts — HMAC-SHA256 with constant-time comparison against X-Hub-Signature-256 header. lib/whatsapp/parse.ts — extracts messages from nested entry[].changes[].value.messages[], normalizes text/image/audio/document/video/location/interactive types, filters out reactions/stickers/contacts. app/api/webhooks/whatsapp/route.ts — GET returns hub.challenge for Meta verification. POST: verify HMAC → parse payload → resolve sender (buildings.whatsapp_phone_number_id → building_id, residents.phone → resident_id) → insert into messages table → rate limit via Redis (10/min/phone) → unknown senders go to contacts_temp for BM review. Always returns 200 to prevent Meta retries. AI processing stub left for T027. Phone resolution handles both +60 and 60 formats via OR query.
DECIDED_BY: claude_code
TASK_REF: T026
