DATE: 2026-03-18T15:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0028c
CATEGORY: architecture
CONTEXT: T027 — Layer 1 Router. DeepSeek V3 classifies inbound messages into 23 intents. Must be fast (~0.2s), deterministic, and never hallucinate intent IDs.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Supabase Edge Function (separate deployment — overkill for single API call)
  2. lib/ai/router.ts as importable module (selected) — called from webhook handler, reusable from Telegram webhook later, testable in isolation
  3. Embedding-based classification (complex, requires training data, slower)
DECISION: Three new files in lib/ai/. types.ts — IntentId union type (23 values), RouterResult, AgentOutput, ConversationState, MessageContext. intents.ts — INTENT_DEFINITIONS array with id, model_tier, keywords, tools, description for all 23 intents + EMERGENCY_KEYWORDS list for fast bypass. router.ts — routeMessage() calls DeepSeek V3 (deepseek-chat, api.deepseek.com) with temperature 0.1 and response_format json_object. Emergency keyword detection runs BEFORE API call — instant bypass to EMERGENCY intent. Response parsing validates intent_id against known set, forces model_tier from our definitions (never trusts model output for tier), clamps confidence 0-1, falls back to GENERAL_ENQUIRY on any error. Confidence < 0.60 auto-routes to GENERAL_ENQUIRY. Webhook handler now calls routeMessage() and updates messages table with ai_intent, ai_model_tier, ai_confidence.
DECIDED_BY: claude_code
TASK_REF: T027
