DECISION_ID: D-0029c
CATEGORY: architecture
CONTEXT: T028 — Conversation state machine. Multi-turn flows (facility booking, visitor registration, etc.) need to persist state across messages. Must check BEFORE Router — if active flow exists, bypass classification entirely.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. In-memory state (lost on restart, no horizontal scaling)
  2. Redis with conversation_state:{phone} key, 10min TTL (selected) — matches existing Redis pattern, auto-expires stale flows
  3. Database table (overkill for ephemeral state with 10min lifetime)
DECISION: Two new files. lib/ai/flows.ts — 6 FlowDefinition objects (FACILITY_BOOKING 4 steps, VISITOR_REGISTER 4 steps, BUTLER_REQUEST 5 steps, RENOVATION_ENQUIRY 5 steps, PAYMENT_CLAIM 3 steps, RENTAL_REQUEST 4 steps). Each step has id, prompt_key, required_entity, next_step. lib/ai/conversation-state.ts — getConversationState() reads Redis before Router, startConversationFlow() begins a new flow (skips steps for entities already collected), advanceConversationFlow() collects entity and moves to next step or completes flow. Cancel keywords (cancel/batal/stop) clear state. Confirmation step recognises yes/ya/ok/sahkan/betul. Webhook handler checks state before Router — if active flow, bypasses classification entirely and continues flow.
DECIDED_BY: claude_code
TASK_REF: T028
