DECISION_ID: D-0151
CATEGORY: schema
CONTEXT: Staff creation succeeded (data saved to DB) but staff list showed empty. BM Add Staff form also used invalid role enum values (accounts, assistant_manager, technician, admin) that don't exist in user_role_type enum.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Debug why GET returns empty despite data existing
  2. Fix role enum values only
DECISION: Root cause was ambiguous FK join — user_roles has TWO foreign keys to users table (user_id and assigned_by). PostgREST returned HTTP 300 Multiple Choices for `users!inner(...)` because it couldn't determine which FK to follow. Fixed by using explicit FK name: `users!user_roles_user_id_fkey(...)`. Also fixed role enum: ROLE_OPTIONS now uses valid enum values (staff/bm/committee). Added Position dropdown for staff sub-role labels (Admin, Accounts, Technician, etc.) stored in KV, not enum. Fixed session.ts ROLE_PRIORITY to only contain valid enum values. Added grouped display (BM/Committee/Staff sections), success toast, error logging.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
