DATE: 2026-03-26T16:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0192
CATEGORY: fix
CONTEXT: Standalone apps (/attendance, /kiosk, /guard, /agm/*) were redirecting BM users to /bm/dashboard. Root cause: middleware had these routes in PROTECTED_PREFIXES with strict role-based ROLE_PATHS checking. BM role only allowed ['/bm', '/kiosk'], so /attendance, /guard were blocked. /agm was not in middleware matcher at all.
DECISION: Split middleware into two route categories: (1) PROTECTED_PREFIXES — portal routes requiring specific role match, (2) ANY_AUTH_PREFIXES — standalone app routes (/attendance, /kiosk, /agm) requiring valid session but allowing ANY role. Removed standalone app paths from ROLE_PATHS since role check is no longer needed for them. Added /agm to middleware matcher. No changes to /bm/settings/apps page — URLs were already correct (using https://minilab.my base).
DECIDED_BY: claude_code
TASK_REF: Session 8.5 Routing Fix
