DATE: 2026-03-27T01:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0210
CATEGORY: architecture
CONTEXT: WhatsApp Reverse OTP built for resident authentication. Zero SMS cost — resident sends OTP TO building via WhatsApp. Flow: resident enters phone on /resident/login → system generates 6-digit code + wa.me link with LOGIN prefix → resident clicks link → WhatsApp opens with code pre-filled → resident sends → existing webhook handleLoginOTP receives code → matches Redis OTP → marks verified → otp-status endpoint polls and detects verification → session created → redirect to /resident. OTP stored in Redis with 10-min TTL using existing otpKey pattern. Rate limited 3/hr/phone. Reuses existing webhook OTP handler (LOGIN XXXXXX format) — no webhook changes needed. New APIs: /api/auth/resident/request-otp (building-aware, resident validation), /api/auth/resident/check-otp (polls session). /api/bm/settings/resident-portal-toggle (GET/PATCH toggle).
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: Session 11 Resident Auth
