CONTEXT: When no admin tool matched a user message (or confidence was low), the AI returned a static menu dump: "Hmm, not sure what you need. Try: change working hours, add contractor..." — making it seem dumb. Greetings like "hi" were routed through the two-stage tool classifier and always got the same fallback. "Can you help me create unit" was not understood because the classifier prompt lacked intent-based examples.
DECISION: Three-layer fix: (1) Greeting detection (Stage 0) bypasses tool system entirely, calls DeepSeek conversationally with building context + last 3 message pairs. (2) No-match/low-confidence fallback replaced static message with generateConversationalResponse() — DeepSeek call with system prompt describing capabilities, personality (casual Malaysian English), and building context. Includes chat history for continuity. (3) Stage 1 classification prompt upgraded from bare category names to intent-based descriptions with natural language examples including Malay. All 19 ai_tools rows expanded with rich keywords (8-19 per tool) and examples (4-10 per tool) including Malaysian English and Malay variations. Cost: ~$0.003 extra per fallback message (DeepSeek, 300 max tokens).
