CONTEXT: The import handler processed each file immediately on upload. No way for BM to upload multiple files and have the AI wait before processing. Real onboarding involves 2-3 data sources (accounting export, access card system, etc.) that need to be merged.
DECISION: Built multi-file import conversation mode using Redis session state machine. Key: import_session:{buildingId}:{userId}, TTL 30 min. States: collecting (waiting for files), mapping (showing column mapping / merge strategy), confirming (waiting for user approval). During collection, each dropped file is parsed and column-mapped immediately but not imported. "Done" triggers merge strategy proposal (DeepSeek, via existing proposeMergeStrategy) for multi-file or direct mapping preview for single file. "Cancel" clears session. Session check in v4-pipeline runs BEFORE greeting detection and intent router so "done"/"that's all"/"dah"/"siap" don't get misclassified. Single file upload without active session creates a session and shows mapping with "Have more files? Drop them now." prompt. Merge uses existing executeMerge() which produces a unified dataset, then executeImport() runs on that. Same handler for web chat and Telegram — keyed on buildingId:userId not channel.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: Multi-file import conversation mode
