CONTEXT: Three bugs found during live testing. (1) Web→Telegram sync silently failed when AI response contained unmatched Markdown chars (* _ `) — Telegram Markdown v1 parser rejects the entire message. (2) ChatBubble rendered raw markdown asterisks as literal text. (3) AI-extracted time values like "2pm)" with trailing parenthesis caused PostgreSQL TIME type insertion error.
DECISION: (1) Strip markdown chars from Telegram sync messages — use plain text instead of parse_mode Markdown for synced messages. (2) Added MessageContent React component with safe regex-based markdown rendering: **bold**, *italic*, \`code\`, \n. No dangerouslySetInnerHTML. (3) Added cleanTimeInput() to strip parentheses, normalize AM/PM spacing, and convert "1pm"→"13:00" / "1:30pm"→"13:30" for PostgreSQL TIME. Applied to working hours handler time extraction.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: Three ChatBubble fixes
