D-0257 | 2026-03-28 | Async AI pipeline — background processing + Supabase Realtime
CONTEXT: The sync chat/send route blocks the HTTP response while the AI pipeline runs (3-8s). This causes Vercel function timeouts on complex queries and poor UX with long spinner waits.
DECISION: Implemented async AI pipeline using Vercel waitUntil(). The webhook returns 200 immediately with messageId; AI processes in background via processMessageInBackground(). Client receives AI response via Supabase Realtime subscription on messages table (filtered by building_id). Added message status state machine (pending→processing→complete/failed). Stuck-message cleanup cron runs every 5 minutes. Sync fallback preserved — if client doesn't send async:true, existing inline pipeline runs. Telegram webhook also uses waitUntil() for background processing. Migration 048 added status column + index + Realtime publication. ChatBubble subscribes to Realtime with 30s safety timeout.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: D-0257
