  1. Custom OAuth with state parameter in URL (complex, need to manage state ourselves)
  2. NextAuth signIn() with callbackUrl containing action+returnTo params (selected — leverages existing NextAuth, minimal new code)
DECISION: Two-context OAuth flow via callbackUrl params. Login: action=login in callbackUrl → /auth/google/complete reads NextAuth session → calls /api/auth/google/callback (now rejects unknown users with 404). Registration: action=register&returnTo=/register/[type] → complete page stores Google profile in temp cookie (15min TTL, httpOnly=false for client read) → redirects to form → GoogleAuthGate component reads cookie and renders pre-filled form. New files: lib/auth/google-register.ts (cookie helpers), lib/auth/portal-router.ts (role→portal mapping), components/auth/GoogleAuthGate.tsx (shared gate). Updated /api/register/vendor and /api/register/hardware-store-application to accept google_* fields, create user with Google data, and mint Redis session on registration. All 7 forms now require Google auth before showing form fields. Email+name read-only from Google, phone still editable.
