DATE: 2026-03-30T16:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0278
CATEGORY: fix
CONTEXT: CHV CSV import of 700+ units showed only ~200 residents in UI. Phone numbers lost leading zero (998/998 phones stored without + prefix). 3 residents had IC number stored as full_name (column mis-mapping by AI). Delete button on /bm/settings/blocks was permanently disabled for all blocks that had units — no cascade delete existed. No reset flow for clean reimport.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Fix residents API cap at 200 (increase to 5000) — selected
  2. Paginate the blocks page residents table — rejected, adds UX complexity for a settings page
DECISION:
  ROOT CAUSES FOUND:
  (1) ~200 residents in UI: GET /api/bm/residents had Math.min(..., 200) hard cap. blocks/page.tsx fetched limit=200. DB had 998 residents — 798 were invisible.
  (2) Phone leading zero lost: legacy import API (/api/bm/residents/import) stored raw phone string with zero normalization. Excel converts 0123456789 to integer 123456789 when column is not text-formatted.
  (3) IC-as-name: AI column mapper occasionally maps IC column to owner_name. Neither import pipeline validated that full_name wasn't a numeric string.
  (4) Delete button broken: button was disabled={unit_count > 0} — all CHV blocks have units so all delete buttons were permanently greyed out. No cascade delete path existed.
  FIXES APPLIED:
  (1) GET cap raised to 5000. blocks/page.tsx and console/page.tsx fetch limit raised to 2000.
  (2) safeNormalizePhone() added to legacy import route — handles +60/60/0/1-prefix/no-prefix MY numbers. formatPhoneForDB() called in POST /api/bm/residents.
  (3) cleanName() validation in import: rejects names that match IC pattern (12 digits) or phone pattern. Redirects value to ic_number/phone field if those are empty. Rows with invalid name are skipped with error message.
  (4) residentDisplayName() utility (lib/utils/resident-label.ts) — safe label for any display, falls back to "Unit X (no name)" for garbage values.
  (5) Block delete API now supports ?cascade=true: deletes residents → nulls unit_id on 16 dependent tables → deletes units → deletes block. GET /api/bm/blocks/[id] returns preflight counts. Frontend shows count-confirmation dialog before cascade.
  (6) New POST /api/bm/import/reset: deletes all residents + units for building. GET /api/bm/import/reset returns counts. Reset All Units button added to Units Overview section in blocks page. Two-step confirmation dialog with CSV tips.
  (7) Legacy import file limit raised 2MB → 5MB.
  Import route (raw_imports vs data_imports): blocks page uses legacy /api/bm/residents/import which logs to data_imports table. Modern multi-step pipeline logs to raw_imports. Both valid paths kept.
  .mcp.json created with correct Supabase project ref nncbsumdmsyjjrgdjjea.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: CHV import fix — phone normalization + name validation + limit cap + block delete cascade + reset all units
