---
DATE: 2026-03-31T08:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0279
CATEGORY: fix
CONTEXT: FIX 2 — reported as "residents imported without unit links". DB query confirmed: 0 unlinked residents (all 998/998 have unit_id set). resident_units junction table does not exist — schema uses residents.unit_id directly. The real latent risk: both import pipelines used bare upsert on (building_id, unit_number) unique constraint. If CSV unit_number format differs from existing DB format (e.g. "A-1-01" vs "CS/A-1-01"), the upsert creates a phantom duplicate unit instead of matching the existing one. This would cause residents to link to the phantom unit, making them invisible in the unit table.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Per-row DB query to find fuzzy match (rejected — too slow for 700+ rows)
  2. Pre-load all existing units into memory, normalize + lookup in-process (selected)
DECISION:
  (1) lib/import/normalize-unit.ts: normalizeUnitNumber() strips separators+uppercases for token comparison. buildUnitLookupMap() builds token→unit map. findExistingUnit() returns fuzzy match or null.
  (2) /api/bm/residents/import (legacy): pre-loads all existing units at import start. Before each upsert: checks fuzzy map first. If match found → uses existing unit_id. If no match → upserts (new unit). Tracks newly-created units that didn't match anything as phantomUnits[]. Returns phantomUnits in response for UI warning.
  (3) lib/import/execute-import.ts (modern pipeline): same pre-load + fuzzy match pattern. Also already had formatPhoneForDB — no phone fix needed here.
  (4) GET /api/bm/residents/unlinked: returns residents where unit_id IS NULL. PATCH: assigns a unit to a specific resident.
  (5) UnlinkedResidentsWarning component in blocks page: amber collapsible banner showing residents with no unit link. Each row has "Assign Unit" button with unit dropdown. Disappears when count = 0.
  (6) ImportSection result panel: shows amber phantomUnits warning if new unit numbers were created that didn't fuzzy-match existing units.
  Repair query for existing unlinked residents documented in session (no rows to repair currently).
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: FIX 2 — fuzzy unit matching + unlinked residents warning UI
