DATE: 2026-03-31T10:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0280
CATEGORY: fix
CONTEXT: CHV CSV import of 700+ residents produced ~200 visible, all phone numbers stored without +60 prefix, some IC numbers stored as resident names, block delete button failing silently, reset API broken.
FINDINGS:
  FINDING 1 — Phone format: All 998 CHV residents stored with bare digits (e.g. "176194618") instead of "+60176194618". Root cause: original import predated normalizePhone code. All 4 affected import paths (old route, execute-import.ts, lib/utils/phone.ts) now produce canonical +60XXXXXXXXX. SQL UPDATE fixed all 998 existing rows. still_bad = 0 confirmed.
  FINDING 2 — IC as name: 3 residents had 12-digit IC stored in full_name (mis-mapped column). cleanName() in old import route already catches this. execute-import.ts (new AI pipeline) lacked this check — added. SQL fixed existing 3 rows: IC moved to ic_number, full_name set to "(name missing — please update)".
  FINDING 3 — Delete button silently failing: /api/bm/blocks/[id] DELETE handler nulled unit_id deps before deleting residents but did NOT null resident_id deps on cases/parcels/facility_bookings/renovation_applications/tenancies/vehicle_logs/visitors/etc. (all NO ACTION FK). If residents had those linked records, resident delete would fail silently, unit delete would fail, block delete would 500. Fixed by fetching resident IDs first, nulling all resident_id FKs, then deleting.
  FINDING 4 — Reset API broken: /api/bm/import/reset/route.ts existed but tried to delete residents before nulling their downstream FK dependencies. Same NO ACTION FK issue as Finding 3. Fixed: null resident_id deps first, then delete residents, then null unit_id deps, then delete units. Error checking added.
  FINDING 5 — lib/utils/phone.ts: normalizePhone() worked correctly but relied on implicit fallback for 1XXXXXXXX. Rewritten with explicit ordered cases: +60 strip, 60X→canonical, 0X→+6X, 1X→+60X, fallback.
DECISION:
  (1) lib/utils/phone.ts: explicit ordered normalization with 4 cases + fallback.
  (2) lib/import/execute-import.ts: added cleanName() with IC/phone pattern detection before inserting residents.
  (3) /api/bm/blocks/[id]/route.ts DELETE: fetch residentIds first, null 14 resident_id FK columns across 10 tables, then delete residents, then proceed.
  (4) /api/bm/import/reset/route.ts POST: same resident FK null-first pattern. Added error returns on resident/unit delete failure.
  (5) SQL fix applied live: 998 phone records corrected, 3 IC-as-name records fixed.
  BM can now use Reset All Units → reimport correct CSV cleanly.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: CHV import fix — phone normalization + name validation + delete cascade + reset endpoint
