DATE: 2026-04-02T12:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0322
CATEGORY: architecture | feature | ai
CONTEXT: V13-5 — AI starts every BM conversation blind (no building context until a tool is called).
  Need a pre-computed building health snapshot injected into the AI system prompt so the AI
  is immediately informed on session start.
DECISION:
  Built a 5-part Building State Snapshot system:
  1. lib/building-state.ts — getBuildingState(buildingId) runs 18 parallel Supabase queries
     (Promise.allSettled, fail gracefully). Covers: building info, unit occupancy (via
     unit_occupancy_status DISTINCT ON via JS dedup), people by role + Telegram-linked count,
     face enrollments, open/stale cases, pending approvals, collection rate + outstanding,
     attendance today, AI/WA credits, expiring insurance/docs/contracts (30d window),
     recent complaints (7d), Telegram groups, last patrol. Output: 11-line plain text <250
     tokens. No PII — only counts, percentages, boolean flags.
     getCachedBuildingState() wraps with Redis TTL=1h. invalidateBuildingState() for mutations.
  2. lib/ai/admin-router.ts — generateConversationalResponse() now fetches the cached building
     state in parallel with other context queries. Injected as "Current Building State
     (auto-updated hourly)" section in the system prompt. Only BM/staff/admin senders reach
     this path (isAdminRole gate in v4-pipeline.ts). Residents are unaffected.
  3. app/api/cron/building-state/route.ts — hourly cron (0 * * * *) invalidates + recomputes
     for all active+trial buildings. Registered in vercel.json.
  4. app/api/bm/building-state/route.ts — GET endpoint returning {state, cached_at, building_id}
     for dashboard use. BM/staff/superadmin roles only.
  5. lib/cache.ts — added buildingState key + 3600s TTL constant for consistency.
  TypeScript notes: credit_balances not in stale types file (as any cast). TS errors: 0.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
