DATE: 2026-04-02T15:00:00Z
DECISION_ID: D-0324
CATEGORY: architecture | feature | schema
CONTEXT: V13-7 — 22+ dumb crons each firing independently for various checks (compliance, credits,
  stale tasks, etc). Need a single intelligent orchestrator that scans holistically, dedupes,
  respects cooldowns, and dispatches consolidated Telegram summaries.
DECISION:
  Built Gap Engine — a daily building health scanner with 6 gap types, upsert-based dedup,
  auto-resolve, and Telegram notification dispatcher.

  1. building_gaps table (migration v13_7_building_gaps):
     - UUID PK, building_id FK, gap_type text, severity (red/amber/green),
       category (people/operations/finance/compliance/setup), entity_id/entity_type for links,
       title, description, suggested_action, action_ui_link, auto_resolve_payload JSONB,
       last_notified_at, cooldown_hours (default 72), resolved_at/resolved_by for auto-resolve.
     - Unique partial index on (building_id, gap_type, entity_id) WHERE resolved_at IS NULL
       for dedup without ON CONFLICT complexity.
     - RLS: BM/staff read via user_roles membership.

  2. lib/gap-engine.ts — scanBuildingGaps(buildingId):
     - 6 parallel gap scanners:
       a. people_no_telegram: staff/guard without telegram_id → amber
       b. people_no_face: staff/guard without face_enrollments row → amber
       c. ops_stale_tasks: cases open >7d with no update → red (>3), amber (1-3)
       d. finance_credits_low: credit_balances balance=0 → red, <20% allowance → amber
       e. compliance_expiring: insurance/building_documents/contractor contracts expiring 30d → red (<7d), amber
       f. setup_incomplete: missing name/address/whatsapp/telegram/email/staff/working_hours → amber
     - Column corrections: building_documents uses expires_at (not expiry_date).
       case_status has no 'cancelled' — filter uses NOT IN ('resolved','closed').
     - upsertGap(): checks for existing unresolved gap and updates, or inserts new.
     - resolveGap(): sets resolved_at=NOW(), resolved_by='auto' when condition clears.

  3. lib/gap-engine-notify.ts — dispatchGapNotifications():
     - Queries unresolved red/amber gaps past their cooldown.
     - Groups by building. Building-level 24h rate limit.
     - Sends consolidated Telegram message (🔴 Urgent / 🟡 Attention sections).
     - Updates last_notified_at on dispatched gap rows.
     - Skips buildings with no BM telegram_id (gaps still visible on dashboard).

  4. app/api/cron/gap-engine/route.ts — daily at 1am UTC (9am MYT).
     - Scans all active+trial buildings in parallel via Promise.allSettled.
     - Calls dispatchGapNotifications() after scanning.
     - Registered in vercel.json.

  5. app/api/bm/gaps/route.ts — GET /api/bm/gaps:
     - Auth: BM/staff/superadmin session.
     - Returns unresolved gaps sorted by severity (red first), with summary counts.

  6. lib/ai/generic-read/allowed-tables.ts — 4 new entries:
     gaps, building_gaps, health, issues — all map to ai_view_gaps.

  7. ai_tools.generic_read keywords expanded: +18 terms (gaps, health check, what needs attention,
     urgent, overdue, expiring, incomplete, building health, daily report, morning brief, issues,
     problems, what is wrong, red flags, alerts, action needed, followup needed, action required).

  TypeScript: 0 errors. Build: see Vercel.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: V13-7 — Gap Engine (proactive building health scanner)
