     - Gap rows: severity dot (red/amber/green), title, category-based action link.
     - Max 5 rows shown; overflow → "View all {n} gaps →" links to /bm/gaps.
     - "All clear" happy path preserved when no gaps exist.
     - Fail-open: API errors fall back to "All clear" state.

  2. /api/bm/gaps/scan route (app/api/bm/gaps/scan/route.ts):
     - POST handler. Auth: BM/staff/superadmin session.
     - Rate limited: 1 scan per building per hour via Redis TTL key gap-scan-cooldown:{buildingId}.
     - Fail-open if Redis unavailable (no rate limit that time).
     - On cooldown: returns current gaps from DB without scanning.
     - On fresh scan: calls scanBuildingGaps(buildingId), then returns fresh gaps.

  3. /bm/gaps page (app/bm/gaps/page.tsx):
     - Full gap list fetching from GET /api/bm/gaps.
     - Summary badges (red urgent / amber warnings / green info counts).
     - Grouped by category (People / Operations / Finance / Compliance / Setup).
     - Each row: severity dot, title, description, suggested_action, action button.
     - No-gaps state: centered checkmark.

  4. get_building_gaps AI handler (lib/ai/actions/admin-handlers.ts):
     - Queries building_gaps WHERE resolved_at IS NULL, limit 10.
     - Sorts red→amber→green. Returns formatted Markdown summary with emoji dots.
     - Registered as Handler 21 (MOA handlers renumbered to 22/23).
     - ai_tools row inserted: scope=admin, category=admin_query, 25 Manglish/Malay keywords.

