DECISION: D-0329 — Face clock-in pre-check + timeout + manual fallback
CONTEXT: /app clock page launched FaceScannerPremium immediately, causing infinite scanning loop for users with zero face enrollments. No timeout existed, and no cancel button was visible during scanning.
SOLUTION:
  1. New GET /api/app/face-status checks face_enrollments for current user (user_id direct + contractor_staff_id path). Returns { enrolled: bool }.
  2. Clock page now starts in 'checking' view, fetches face-status on mount. If not enrolled → shows 'not_enrolled' card (dark #111 bg, ShieldAlert icon, no self-enroll, single Manual Clock In/Out button). If enrolled → shows scanner. Fail-open on API error.
  3. returnViewRef tracks which view to return to after performClock succeeds/fails (not_enrolled → back to not_enrolled, scanner → back to scanner, manual → back to manual).
  4. FaceScannerPremium: new props onCancel? and timeoutMs? (default 30s). 30s scanTimeoutRef fires on mount when scanning begins; on trigger stops camera/loops, sets phase='timeout', shows timeout UI (Try Again restarts via retryKey, Manual Clock-In calls onCancel). Cancel button shown in top bar during all active scan phases.
TRADE-OFFS: Fail-open on face-status API error means users with network issues still see the scanner (better UX than blocking all clock-ins). No self-enroll — admin-only per existing design decision.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
