CONTEXT: Need complete leave management for all staff types (building staff, guards, cleaners, contractor workers). Each staff type has a different employer, so approval must route to the correct authority.
SOLUTION:
  1. Schema: 3 new tables — leave_policies (per building/org, leave types + entitlements), leave_balances (per user per year, tracks entitled/used/carried_forward), leave_requests (submissions with status pending/approved/rejected/cancelled).
  2. Approval routing matrix:
     - Building staff (no PMC) → BM approves
     - Building staff (with PMC) → PMC admin approves, BM read-only
     - Guards → security_admin approves
     - Cleaners → cleaning_admin approves
     - Contractor workers → contractor_admin approves
  3. APIs: POST /api/app/leave (submit), GET /api/app/leave (balances + history), PATCH /api/app/leave/[id] (cancel), GET/PATCH /api/leave/approve (approver inbox), GET /api/bm/leave (BM read-only all-building), GET /api/bm/leave/calendar (calendar view), GET/PATCH /api/bm/leave/policies (BM policy edit).
  4. PWA pages (dark #0A0A0A): /app/leave (apply + recent), /app/leave/history, /app/leave/approvals (for org admins).
  5. BM desktop page: 3-tab (Requests / Calendar / Policies). Calendar uses pure Tailwind grid with TYPE_COLORS.
  6. Portal leave pages: /security/leave, /cleaning/leave, /contractor/leave (identical approve UI).
  7. Telegram notifications: notifyLeaveSubmitted() to approver(s) on submission; notifyLeaveDecision() to applicant on approve/reject.
  8. AI: ai_view_leave mapped in generic-read for keywords leave/leave_requests/cuti. building-state snapshot includes on-leave count today.
TRADE-OFFS: Balance auto-creation on first GET (ensureBalances helper) avoids admin setup step. Stale database.types.ts requires `(supabaseAdmin as any).from('table')` pattern for all 3 new tables.
