DATE: 2026-04-04T00:00:00Z
DECISION: D-0338 — Face clock-in overhaul: no manual, simplified liveness, auto-clock on match
CONTEXT: Scanner stalled at 55% due to strict blink-detection liveness (required 2 blinks via EAR algorithm). Manual clock-in violated the "face IS the identity" principle. face-status API checked the logged-in user's enrollment instead of building-level readiness. Matched view required user to tap a button to confirm clock-in.
SOLUTION:
  1. Liveness simplified: replaced blink detection (EAR threshold, 2 blinks in 10s) with "3 consecutive frames with face detected". Liveness now passes in ~100ms. No head turn, no blink required. Data overlay shows FRAMES: X/3 instead of BLINK/EAR values.
  2. Manual clock-in removed entirely: ViewState no longer has 'manual' or 'matched'. All manual-related state, functions, JSX deleted (openManual, handleManualClock, handleDirectManualClock, selectedStaff, manualStaffList, loadingManual, ChevronDown/LogIn/LogOut imports).
  3. Auto-clock on match: handleMatch() now immediately calls /api/attendance/clock — no intermediate confirmation step. Scanner result_match → clock API → success screen.
  4. Success screen: shows "Welcome, {name}!" + time. Auto-navigates to /app after 3s via router.push.
  5. face-status API changed: now checks COUNT of active face_enrollments for session.buildingId (building-level readiness). Returns { has_enrollments, enrollment_count }. Fail-open on error.
  6. no_enrollments view: replaces old not_enrolled. Shows "No faces enrolled" message, no buttons (no manual fallback). Admin must enroll via /bm/staff.
  7. result_nomatch screen in FaceScannerPremium: added "Try Again" retry button (was missing). Timeout screen: removed "Manual Clock-In" button, only "Try Again" remains.
  8. Console logs added at every step for debugging.
TRADE-OFFS: 3-frame liveness is less fraud-resistant than blink detection (a printed photo held steady for 3 frames would pass). Acceptable trade-off for staff-only internal use where liveness is a convenience check, not a security gate. Can be tightened later.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: Face clock-in overhaul
