DATE: 2026-04-04T00:00:00Z
DECISION: D-0340 — attendance status refresh after clock-in + attendance history page
CONTEXT: Two bugs in Staff PWA (/app): (1) Home page attendance card showed "Not clocked in yet" even after successful face clock-in. After redirect router.push('/app'), Next.js App Router served cached component state so fetchClock() didn't re-run. (2) /app/my-attendance called /api/attendance/history which didn't exist — 404 every time.
SOLUTION:
  1. app/app/clock/page.tsx: Changed router.push('/app') to router.push('/app?t=' + Date.now()). Timestamp param busts Next.js router cache, forcing component remount.
  2. app/app/page.tsx: Added useSearchParams hook + Suspense wrapper. Added searchParams to useEffect dependency array so fetchClock() re-runs whenever ?t= changes.
  3. app/api/attendance/history/route.ts: Created new GET endpoint. Accepts building_id + user_id or staff_id. Returns last N records with clock_in_at, clock_out_at, method, face_match_score, is_late, is_early_departure.
  4. app/app/my-attendance/page.tsx: Rewrote with correct API path + improved UI: "This Week" section (last 7 days with per-day cards), "This Month" summary (present/absent/late counts), "All Records" full history. Shows face match score % when available.
TRADE-OFFS: useSearchParams requires Suspense boundary — wrapped outer export. The ?t= param is ignored by the page logic but serves as a cache-bust signal via searchParams dependency. Monthly absent count approximates working days (excludes weekends) without holiday calendar — acceptable for MVP.
