DATE: 2026-04-04T00:00:00Z
DECISION: D-0341 — handle 409 as already-clocked-in + support clock-out flow
CONTEXT: Face clock-in matched at 82.1% but showed "Clock-in failed. Please try again." because the API returned HTTP 409 (duplicate clock-in — user already clocked in that day). The page treated all non-2xx responses as errors. Additionally, no handling existed for the fully-completed state (both clock-in and clock-out recorded today).
SOLUTION:
  1. app/api/attendance/clock/route.ts: Added clock_in_at to the 409 response body so the client can display "already clocked in at HH:MM" without a separate fetch.
  2. app/app/clock/page.tsx: Added two new ViewStates — already_clocked_in (clocked in, not yet out) and already_completed (both recorded today).
  3. checkClockState now detects clock_out_at in the response → sets already_completed view (skips scanner entirely).
  4. handleMatch 409 handler: sets already_clocked_in view instead of clock_error. Shows "Already clocked in at HH:MM" with "Clock Out Now" button (returns to scanner, clockState.clocked_in=true so handleMatch sends clock_out action) and "Back to Home" link.
  5. already_completed view shows both clock-in and clock-out times, no scan needed.
  6. Success view updated: "Welcome, X!" for clock-in, "Goodbye, X!" for clock-out. Dark theme applied consistently (removed stray Tailwind green/muted classes).
TRADE-OFFS: clockState race condition (match fires before checkClockState resolves → null clockState → sends clock_in → 409) is now handled gracefully instead of blocked. Blocking would require gating the scanner on clockState resolution, adding latency. Grace handling is simpler and sufficient.
DECIDED_BY: human + claude
TASK_REF: Hotfix — 409 already-clocked-in handling + clock-out flow
