DECISION_ID: D-0347
CATEGORY: architecture
CONTEXT: Attendance clock-in/out broken for contractor staff without linked user accounts. Root cause identified in audit (docs/attendance-audit-v13.md): find_open_attendance and count_today_sessions RPCs filter WHERE al.user_id = p_user_id — in SQL, NULL = NULL is always FALSE, so contractor-only staff (user_id IS NULL) could never clock out. Every face scan created a new duplicate clock-in.
OPTIONS_CONSIDERED:
  1. Add COALESCE/IS NOT DISTINCT FROM logic — rejected (fragile, doesn't handle dual-ID lookup)
  2. Add p_contractor_staff_id parameter with OR logic to all affected RPCs — selected (clean, explicit, backward-compatible via DEFAULT NULL)
DECISION: Migration 058 (fix_attendance_rpcs_null_user_id). Four RPCs patched with dual-path WHERE clause:
  1. find_open_attendance(p_building_id, p_user_id DEFAULT NULL, p_contractor_staff_id DEFAULT NULL) — WHERE (p_user_id IS NOT NULL AND user_id = p_user_id) OR (p_contractor_staff_id IS NOT NULL AND contractor_staff_id = p_contractor_staff_id)
  2. count_today_sessions — same dual-path pattern
  3. get_attendance_today — same dual-path pattern
  4. get_attendance_history — same dual-path pattern
  Old 2-arg overloads dropped (they had p_user_id as first positional arg). The _by_staff variants (get_attendance_today_by_staff, get_attendance_history_by_staff) were NOT changed — they already filter by contractor_staff_id correctly.
  Clock API (app/api/attendance/clock/route.ts) updated: all 3 RPC calls now pass both p_user_id and p_contractor_staff_id. PostgREST today_minutes query replaced with get_attendance_today RPC call. Zero PostgREST reads remain in clock API (2 writes: .update for clock-out, .insert for clock-in — acceptable).
DECIDED_BY: claude_code
TASK_REF: Fix attendance RPCs NULL user_id bug (BUG-1, BUG-2, BUG-3 from audit)

